        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The new Yellow-stage message does not include the ADR-required upgrade hint for how to resolve the warning before merge. At this line it only says the merge gate will block `until resolved`, so callers lose the actionable guidance promised in D8.6 / the review brief for declared Yellow findings.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/domain/src/tddd/catalogue.rs",
              "line": 1056,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:b3d3daf696bfc84ae3f1736d565adcfcc41cfc30e811e15ac32421ebe3aff164",
          "at": "2026-04-12T03:15:43Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The declared-Yellow branch does not include the required upgrade hint in its warning/error text. The briefing/ADR requires Yellow findings to name the declared types and tell callers how to upgrade them before merge, but this message only says the merge gate will block `until resolved`, so users lose the actionable remediation contract in both strict and interim modes.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/domain/src/tddd/catalogue.rs",
              "line": 1055,
              "category": null
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:b3d3daf696bfc84ae3f1736d565adcfcc41cfc30e811e15ac32421ebe3aff164",
          "at": "2026-04-12T03:17:16Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The new Yellow-gate message hardcodes \"Implement the listed type(s)\" as the remediation, but Yellow is also emitted for valid `Delete` entries that are still present in code. In that case the correct fix is to remove the type, not implement it, so the gate will return misleading guidance for a supported domain-type workflow.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/domain/src/tddd/catalogue.rs",
              "line": 1056,
              "category": null
            }
          ],
