          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:7798f5105f96a250904d1abc84fb6aada16d32780868270b58f84a7efe62dc26",
          "at": "2026-04-12T02:09:22Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "ADR D4.3 says the CI path can get fail-closed path safety by calling `reject_symlinks_below` before `read_to_string`, but that helper only detects filesystem symlinks. A checked-out git submodule appears as a normal directory, so `track/items/<id>/spec.json` inside a submodule would still be read successfully even though the truth table later says case #18 is BLOCKED. The plan needs an explicit CI-side submodule guard or the fail-closed table is overstated.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/adr/2026-04-12-1200-strict-spec-signal-gate-v2.md",
              "line": 187,
              "category": "architecture"
            },
            {
              "message": "The approved acceptance criterion for `validate_branch_ref` no longer requires rejecting control characters, even though D4.2 and task T004 describe control-char rejection as part of the contract. An implementation can satisfy the current spec while still accepting refs with embedded `\\n`/NUL, leaving the `origin/{branch}:...` pre-validation incomplete.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/strict-signal-gate-v2-2026-04-12/spec.json",
              "line": 314,
              "category": "validation"
            },
            {
              "message": "`spec.json` still cites `.claude/rules/07-dev-environment.md` and `track/tech-stack.md` as direct sources for the layer/build requirement instead of tracing that requirement back through this ADR. That breaks the stated ADR-only source attribution for this track and means an external convention edit can change the approved basis of the spec without any ADR update.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/strict-signal-gate-v2-2026-04-12/spec.json",
              "line": 248,
              "category": "traceability"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:7798f5105f96a250904d1abc84fb6aada16d32780868270b58f84a7efe62dc26",
          "at": "2026-04-12T02:15:26Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The ADR is self-contradictory about layer ownership: the Context says this redesign will place the gate logic under `libs/infrastructure/src/verify/`, but D5/D9 and the rest of the track move orchestration into `libs/usecase`. Leaving the source-of-truth ADR split like this makes it easy to implement the gate in infrastructure again and violate the intended hexagonal boundary.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/adr/2026-04-12-1200-strict-spec-signal-gate-v2.md",
              "line": 21,
              "category": "architecture"
            },
            {
              "message": "D2.0 defines `validate_branch_ref` as a domain API returning `RefValidationError`, but D4.2 redefines the same function as `Result<(), GateError>`. That ambiguity leaks a gate-specific error type back into the domain contract and gives implementers two incompatible signatures to follow.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/adr/2026-04-12-1200-strict-spec-signal-gate-v2.md",
              "line": 168,
              "category": "architecture"
            },
            {
              "message": "The T004 acceptance criterion no longer covers control-character rejection, even though D4.2 and task T004 both require `validate_branch_ref` to reject control bytes. As written, the spec can be satisfied without testing one of the fail-closed branch-name cases the ADR calls out.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/strict-signal-gate-v2-2026-04-12/spec.json",
              "line": 314,
              "category": "testing"
            },
            {
              "message": "The out-of-scope race-condition item hardcodes `SEC-18` as the follow-up TODO id. The briefing explicitly requires describing this race without assigning a SEC number because numbering is deferred; if another SEC is created first, this plan will immediately point at the wrong follow-up identifier.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/strict-signal-gate-v2-2026-04-12/spec.json",
              "line": 161,
              "category": "traceability"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:7798f5105f96a250904d1abc84fb6aada16d32780868270b58f84a7efe62dc26",
          "at": "2026-04-12T02:19:24Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "T004 now requires `validate_branch_ref` to reject both `:` and control characters, but the planned domain test budget is still only `D14–D20`, and the ADR matrix behind those IDs never exercises either input. As written, the implementation can satisfy the tracked tests while leaving two fail-closed branches unverified.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/strict-signal-gate-v2-2026-04-12/spec.json",
              "line": 314,
              "category": "testing"
            },
            {
              "message": "The spec was updated to defer the wait-and-merge follow-up to 'the next available SEC number', but D7 in the ADR still hardcodes `SEC-18` as the next slot. That leaves the planning artifacts inconsistent and reintroduces the stale-numbering problem this cleanup was supposed to remove.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "knowledge/adr/2026-04-12-1200-strict-spec-signal-gate-v2.md",
              "line": 556,
              "category": "traceability"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:62d04f341c57ef472168edae566a5ad5384f5258c40cb2fa3de47c1ccf2df6b8",
          "at": "2026-04-12T02:24:01Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`verification.md` still defines T004 as only `D14–D20 tests`, even though the ADR, spec, and metadata were expanded to require `D21` (`:`) and `D22` (control character) rejection. As written, this track can be signed off without verifying the two newly added fail-closed branch-ref cases.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/strict-signal-gate-v2-2026-04-12/verification.md",
              "line": 8,
              "category": "testing"
            }
          ],
