        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The derived `track_id` is never validated. `validate_branch_ref` accepts branches like `track/`, `track//foo`, or `track/UPPER`, and those values are passed straight into the reader as `track_id`. That makes the gate consult malformed `track/items/<track_id>/...` paths instead of failing closed.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/usecase/src/merge_gate.rs",
              "line": 104,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:52a140a5d3fa3184f2b69afe438fdf2c8489c03b3e9440928898d06af5db4615",
          "at": "2026-04-12T03:57:24Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:52a140a5d3fa3184f2b69afe438fdf2c8489c03b3e9440928898d06af5db4615",
          "at": "2026-04-12T03:58:51Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`MockTrackBlobReader` ignores both `branch` and `track_id`, so the new tests never verify the key port contract that `check_strict_merge_gate()` must pass the original branch ref to the reader while stripping only the `track/` prefix for `track_id`. A regression in either argument would still leave U1-U18 green, even though the adapter would start reading the wrong `origin/{branch}:track/items/{track_id}/...` blobs. Add a test/mock that records and asserts the received arguments.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/usecase/src/merge_gate.rs",
              "line": 172,
              "category": "tests"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:52a140a5d3fa3184f2b69afe438fdf2c8489c03b3e9440928898d06af5db4615",
          "at": "2026-04-12T04:01:26Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`track/` branches are never validated beyond the generic ref check, so malformed slugs like `track/`, `track//foo`, or `track/UPPER` are passed straight through as `track_id` to the reader. That makes the gate consult `track/items/<raw suffix>/...` instead of failing closed on invalid track branches; validate the `track/` suffix with the domain track-id rules before calling the port.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/usecase/src/merge_gate.rs",
              "line": 104,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:97ceb7fdfaa729d4fc06cd722bc16ad5fe76b6ac064eabbc6d979b6df6b6e8e8",
          "at": "2026-04-12T04:04:42Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`with_unreachable_dt` does not actually make Stage 2 unreachable: it preloads a normal `FetchError`, so if `check_strict_merge_gate` regressed and kept calling `read_domain_types_document` after a Stage 1 failure, these tests would still see a generic blocked outcome instead of detecting the extra read. Use a panic-on-call or call-count asserting stub here so the short-circuit contract is observable.",
